      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__transport_1ga1fdffc6559c7a303cf202406d4eb4f8c" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>VLC_API void</type>
        <definition>VLC_API void vlc_tls_SessionDelete</definition>
        <argsstring>(vlc_tls_t *)</argsstring>
        <name>vlc_tls_SessionDelete</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group__transport_1gad9e89acad0e40f270f6e07cacba4be19" kindref="member">vlc_tls_t</ref> *</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Destroys a TLS session down.</para>
<para>All resources associated with the TLS session are released.</para>
<para>If the session was established successfully, then shutdown cleanly, the underlying socket can be reused. Otherwise, it must be closed. Either way, this function does not close the underlying socket: Use vlc_tls_Close() instead to close it at the same.</para>
<para>This function is non-blocking and is not a cancellation point. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
